s's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh de Monington Lord of Monington was born in 1315, in Nevern, Pembrokeshire, Wales. He married Eleanor Lawton in 1349. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 3 daughters. He died after 1350."},"et":{"1315–after 1350":"1315–pärast 1350","1324–Female":"1324–Surnud","1350–1387":"1350–1387","1362–Male":"1362–Surnud","1373–1421":"1373–1421","–Female":"Surnud","1315–1350":"1315–1350","1349":"1349","1315":"1315","1324":"1324","1421":"1421","1387":"1387","after 1350":"pärast 1350","1373":"1373","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","about 1350":"umbes 1350","Nevern, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Nevern, Pembrokeshire, Wales","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"1315–after 1350":"1315–1350 jälkeen","1324–Female":"1324–Kuollut","1350–1387":"1350–1387","1362–Male":"1362–Kuollut","1373–1421":"1373–1421","–Female":"Kuollut","1315–1350":"1315–1350","1349":"1349","1315":"1315","1324":"1324","1421":"1421","1387":"1387","after 1350":"1350 jälkeen","1373":"1373","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","about 1350":"noin 1350","Nevern, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Nevern, Pembrokeshire, Wales","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England"},"fr":{"1315–after 1350":"1315–après 1350","1324–Female":"1324–Décédée","1350–1387":"1350–1387","1362–Male":"1362–Décédé","1373–1421":"1373–1421","–Female":"Décédée","1315–1350":"1315–1350","1349":"1349","1315":"1315","1324":"1324","1421":"1421","1387":"1387","after 1350":"après 1350","1373":"1373","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","about 1350":